// `abs(x)` source modifier — NV40 FP encodes as SRC0_ABS bit 29.
//
// the reference compiler emits:  MOVH R0, |f[COL0]|; END
//
// Two encoding deltas vs identity_f.cg:
//   - word 1 bit 29 (SRC0_ABS) = 1
//   - word 0 bits 22-23 (PRECISION) = 1 (FP16)
// The precision switch is a the reference compiler optimization — MOV with ANY
// source modifier uses FP16 precision even when the destination is
// R0/fp32.  Verified by byte probes of abs() and -() independently.
void main(
    float4 vcol      : COLOR,
    out float4 color : COLOR)
{
    color = abs(vcol);
}
